<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-695-597  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 695 597.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Information Week  Dec 10 1990 n299 p56(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A natural for Microsoft: increases stake in English-languageinterface vendor. (Natural Language Inc.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Todd, Daniel.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Microsoft has invested another $1 million in Natural Language Inc(NLI), a vendor of English-language interfaces.andP;  This increasesthe Microsoft investment in NLI to between 10 and 15 percent.andP;  Theinvestment adds credence to Microsoft CEO William Gates' call for'information at your fingertips' and highlights Microsoft'sdetermination to achieve simple end-user access to manyinformation sources in a timely fashion.andP;  It also extendsMicrosoft's rights to embed NLI technology into its applicationsand makes cooperative development possible between the twocompanies.andP;  NLI Pres Tania Amochaev states efforts will be focusedon extended English-language access to other sources beyondrelational databases and may include object-oriented and othertechnologies.andP;  The investment may be one of Microsoft's smartestmoves, if the results are indeed 'Information at your fingertips.'andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (Investment activities)Natural Language Inc. (Ownership).andO;Topic:     InvestmentsProduct DevelopmentOwnershipNatural Language InterfacesSoftware Publishers.andO;Feature:   illustrationportrait.andO;Caption:   Tania Amochaev. (portrait)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>